1️⃣ Hiring Manager Round (Most Important Now)

This round is usually 30–45 minutes. The manager wants to check:

Can you own features independently

How you think about system design

How you work with teams

Whether you can communicate with clients

Common questions they may ask

1. Tell me about yourself.
Structure it like this:

Experience: “I have 5.2 years of experience in Ruby on Rails development.”

Skills: Rails, APIs, PostgreSQL, Redis, Sidekiq, AWS, etc.

Projects: Payment integration (Razorpay), background services, email notifications.

Current role responsibilities.

